    {
      "id": "RQ-0040",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Fix record start copy so it does not claim a missing recording was saved",
      "description": "A dogfood run found `record start` messaging confusing because the wrapper rendered wording like `Saved recording: ... not found on disk` even though recordings are only written after `record stop`. The presentation layer currently labels every video artifact as `Saved recording` and appends `not found on disk` whenever the artifact path does not exist, with tests only covering `record stop`. Minimal fix is to make record subcommand-aware copy: keep `record stop` as saved recording, but render `record start` as a lifecycle state such as `Recording started; output will be written on stop: <path>` without treating the not-yet-created file as an error.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "recording",
        "presentation",
        "ux"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "/tmp/feedback.txt",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "npm run verify"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "feedback: /tmp/feedback.txt:11-15 :: recording start reported wording like `Saved recording: ... not found on disk`; feedback suggests `Recording started; output will be written on stop`.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts:496-535 :: video artifacts always format as `Saved recording`, and missing files append `not found on disk`.",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts:1217-1239 :: artifact extraction and summary generation happen generically for all path-bearing commands before any record lifecycle-specific presentation.",
        "path: test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts:371-432 :: metadata-first artifact tests cover `record stop` with `Saved recording: recording.webm`, but there is no `record start` case.",
        "command: npm run verify :: passed 170 tests, 0 failed, 1 skipped; baseline is green before adding lifecycle-copy coverage."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Confirm the installed upstream `record start <path>` JSON shape using the real-upstream test fixture or a fake-upstream fixture before changing presentation logic.",
        "Update record artifact formatting to distinguish `record start` from `record stop`, preserving current saved-copy behavior for completed recordings.",
        "Add focused presentation tests for `record start` and `record stop`, including the not-yet-present output path case.",
        "If user-facing docs mention recording output, align them with the new lifecycle wording.",
        "Verify by running `npm run verify` and confirming record presentation tests pass."
      ],
