      "title": "Review artifact retention limits for screenshot and video-heavy dogfood workflows",
      "description": "The feedback reports hitting the 30 recent artifacts cap quickly while collecting screenshots/videos during dogfooding. Current manifest behavior intentionally bounds recent session artifacts at 30 entries and reports live/evicted counts, but user-facing docs do not make the cap or dogfood workflow impact prominent. Minimal fix is to decide whether the default retention window should be larger or configurable for artifact-heavy QA, document the behavior clearly, and add/update eviction tests for any behavior change.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "artifacts",
        "dogfood",
        "retention"
      ],
